        title: "Rooftop • 3BR/3BA • Modern • Near Capitol Hill",
        description:
          "Experience D.C. from above! This spacious 3BR/3BA home near Capitol Hill features a private rooftop deck with breathtaking views of the National Mall, Ronald Reagan Airport, and Air Force Memorial. Enjoy stunning sunsets, a fully equipped kitchen, modern living spaces, and easy access to D.C.’s top monuments, museums, dining, and entertainment, perfect for families and groups.\n \n✔ 3 Comfortable Bedrooms\n✔ Fully Equipped Kitchen\n✔ Roof Deck\n✔ Smart TVs\n✔ High-Speed Wi-Fi\n✔ Washer/Dryer\n✔ Parking\n\nThe space\nAs soon as you step foot in this gorgeous home, you're greeted by the beautiful yet highly comfortable open-concept living area, elegantly decorated to complement the fantastic DC location.\n \nThe gourmet kitchen blends with the dining area, offering a place to cook and enjoy tasty delicacies before unwinding in the living room, setting the scene for memorable evenings. Sunlight bursts through many windows, making the home bright during the day, accenting the stylish furniture, and enriching the pleasant setting.\n \nRecharge in the three comfortable bedrooms, which boast high-end comforts that allow you to rest after an exciting day of sightseeing.\n \nBut wait! The best is yet to come! Climb to the sun-soaked rooftop deck to marvel at the panoramic city views and catch a breath of fresh air in complete privacy.\n \nThere's so much to do in this inviting home. We look forward to you experiencing its complete coziness and comfort.\n \n★ LIVING ROOM ★\nYou will feel right at home! Sink into the comfy sofa, watch your favorite show, or plan your upcoming Washington adventures.\n \n✔ Comfortable Sofa with Pillows\n✔ Smart TV\n✔ Stylish Coffee Tables\n \n★ KITCHEN & DINING ★\nThis fully equipped kitchen boasts modern appliances, making it easy to whip up anything from delicious breakfasts to gourmet dinners. With ample countertops, you'll have plenty of room to showcase your culinary skills.\n \n✔ Kitchen Island with Bar Stools\n✔ Microwave\n✔ Stove\n✔ Oven\n✔ Toaster\n✔ Blender \n✔ Coffee Maker\n✔ Hot Water Kettle\n✔ Double-Door Refrigerator/Freezer\n✔ Dishwasher\n✔ Sink - Hot & Cold Water\n✔ Plates\n✔ Glasses\n✔ Silverware\n✔ Pots & Pans\n \nCatch up with your loved ones on the lavish rooftop deck while the food gets ready. When done, gather at the kitchen bar and savor a delicious meal in an inviting atmosphere.\n \n★ SLEEPING ARRANGEMENTS – 3 BEDROOMS \nAfter an exciting day of exploring thrilling attractions and historical landmarks, you will look to rest for an equally entertaining tomorrow. Once you are ready to relax, please make your way to these comfortable bedrooms.\n \n♛ Master Bedroom (Upper Floor): Casper California King-Size Bed, Ensuite Bathroom\n♛ Bedroom 2 (Upper Floor): Casper Queen-Size Bed\n♛ Bedroom 3 (Main Floor): Casper  Queen-Size Bed\n \nAll bedrooms are equipped with similar amenities.\n \n✔ Casper Mattresses, Sheets, and Pillows\n✔ Closets with Hangers and Shelves\n✔ Night Stands with Reading Lamps\n \n★ BATHROOMS ★\nIn addition to the master bedroom's ensuite bathroom, the home features two full bathrooms catering to the living area and the remaining bedrooms. All are stocked with pampering towels and necessities to ensure a carefree stay. \n \n✔ Walk-In Shower\n✔ Bathtub with a Shower\n✔ Vanity (Double in the Master Bathroom)\n✔ Mirror\n✔ Toilet\n✔ Towels\n✔ Hair Dryer\n✔ Essential Toiletries\n \n★ ROOFTOP DECK ★ \nStunning Rooftop Views of DC Landmarks & Sunsets\n\nA stunning retreat wouldn’t be complete without a private space to take in the serenity and beauty of the outdoors. From the private rooftop deck, enjoy some of the most breathtaking views in Washington, D.C.  watch planes take off and land at Ronald Reagan National Airport, capture unobstructed sunsets over the National Mall, and on clear days, admire the Air Force Memorial in Arlington in the distance.\n\n✔ Rooftop Lounge Seating Area – the perfect spot for morning coffee, golden hour relaxation, or #InstaWorthy skyline photos.\n\nFind your happiness in this inviting getaway  a peaceful escape from the everyday where you can unwind on the roof deck, relax on the sofa, and enjoy the perfect blend of comfort and convenience while exploring all that Washington, D.C. has to offer. \n\nDon't hesitate to contact us with any questions you may have. Happy Travels!\n\nGuest access\nThe 3-bedroom unit is exclusively yours —no interruptions during your stay —so relax, unwind, and make yourself at home.\n \nOther than the already mentioned amenities, our home also comes with the following:\n \n✔ High-Speed Wi-Fi\n✔ Air Conditioning\n✔ Heating\n✔ Washer/Dryer\n✔ Free Parking\n\nOther things to note\nThe property is located in the Fairlawn neighborhood of Washington, D.C., a welcoming residential community that offers both a peaceful retreat and easy access to the city’s most famous attractions.\n\nJust across the Anacostia River from Capitol Hill, Fairlawn gives you the best of both worlds: a quiet, family-friendly setting with quick connections to downtown D.C. Guests can reach iconic landmarks like the U.S. Capitol, the National Mall, and the Smithsonian Museums in just minutes by car, rideshare, or Metro.\n\nFairlawn is known for its green spaces and local character. Nearby, you’ll find Anacostia Park and the Riverwalk Trail, perfect for walking, jogging, biking, or enjoying a picnic by the water. When it’s time to dine out, explore local restaurants within the community or take a short trip to nearby neighborhoods like Eastern Market, Navy Yard, or The Wharf for a wide variety of dining, cafes, and nightlife.\n\nLocal amenities make your stay even more convenient. Grocery stores, small shops, and everyday essentials are close at hand, while unique boutiques and local businesses offer an authentic D.C. neighborhood experience. Fairlawn’s blend of residential charm, accessibility, and proximity to top attractions makes it an excellent choice for travelers seeking a true Washington, D.C. vacation rental experience.\n\n***Distance times are calculated if traveling by car.\n\n✔ United States Capitol (8 min away)\n✔ Audi Field (8 min away)\n✔ Nats Stadium (7 min away)\n✔ The Wharf DC (10 min away)\n✔ The MGM Harbor Hotel and Casino (10 min away)\n✔ Bolling Air Force Base (8 min away)\n✔ National Gallery of Art (8 min away)\n✔ Washington Monument (8 min away)\n✔ The White House (9 min away)\n✔ Lincoln Memorial (10 min away)\n✔ Downtown D.C (10 min away)\n✔ U Street (12 min away)\n✔ National Zoo (16 min away)\n✔ Rock Creek Park (22 min away)\n✔ Walter Reed National Military Medical Center (28 min away)\n \n\nThe neighborhood is serviced by the Orange and Blue lines at the Potomac Avenue and Eastern Market metro stations and several bus routes. For those preferring to explore on two wheels, the city's bike-sharing services are conveniently available, ensuring smooth transit to nearby attractions.\n \n✔ Metro\n✔ Bus\n✔ Taxi\n✔ Uber & Lyft\n \nIf you are flying in/out of D.C., the best way would be at one of the below airports:\n \n✔ Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport (8 min away)\n✔ Washington Dulles International Airport (30 min away)\n✔ Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport (38 min away)\n\nRegistration Details\nHosted License: 5007242201003541\nShow more",
