        title: "Asteroid City Suite. 3 BR Home Steps from Metro",
        description:
          'Stay in the Asteroid City Suite — a one-of-a-kind Wes Anderson–inspired rowhome in the heart of Capitol Hill, one of the nation’s most iconic neighborhoods. This stylish 3BR retreat features luxury finishes and a fully equipped kitchen.\n- 5 min walk: Potomac Metro + 5 restaurants/bars + grocery store\n- 15 min walk: 50+ restaurants/bars + Barracks Row + Eastern Market + Lincoln Park\n- 30 min walk: U.S. Capitol + National Mall + RFK Festival Grounds + Nationals Park\n\nThe space\nLocated on the first and second floors of a classic 1911 Capitol Hill rowhome, the Asteroid City Suite lets you live like a local in one of DC’s most historic neighborhoods.\nLIVING ROOM: Bright and stylish with curated artwork and a 75" smart TV — perfect for streaming your favorite Wes Anderson film. The modular couch is large, comfy, and great for large groups.\nKITCHEN: Fully equipped with modern appliances, cookware, and dining essentials, plus a spacious, light-filled layout for cooking at home.\nDINING AREA: Open concept with a table for six and a breakfast bar with four stools — ideal for family meals or group gatherings.\nBEDROOM 1: Primary suite with a king bed, en-suite bathroom, dedicated office nook, and ample closet space.\nBEDROOM 2: Cozy middle bedroom with twin-over-twin bunk beds, a reading nook, and a secured shelf stocked with kids’ games and toys.\nBEDROOM 3: Queen bed with closet space and a 55" smart TV.\nSECOND FLOOR HALL: Full bathroom plus washer and dryer for guest use.\nAMENITIES: Fast 1GB WiFi, front porch seating, and a fenced side yard with cornhole and Giant Connect 4 (shared).\n\nGuest access\nEnjoy privacy and convenience with easy self-check-in. The home accommodates up to eight guests, and security cameras are in place at the front and back entrances for everyone’s safety. Please respect house rules by not bringing pets or additional guests unless arranged in advance.\n\nParking in the neighborhood is street-only. While I can’t guarantee a spot in front of the house, I’ve personally never had to park more than a block away. The neighborhood has two types of restrictions: free two-hour parking and residential permit parking. Both are unmetered. I can provide you with one Visitor Parking Permit (VPP), which allows free, unrestricted parking throughout Zone 6—the neighborhood’s designated zone—in both types of spaces.\n\nOther things to note\nPlease note that the Asteroid City Suite is a classic DC rowhome with a separate basement unit and an attached neighboring house. We kindly ask that you respect the privacy of others in the building and next door by keeping noise to a minimum, especially during quiet hours.\n\nPlease note that the home includes stairs, which may not be suitable for guests with mobility limitations.\n\nRegistration Details\nHosted License: 5007242201005598\nUnhosted License: 5007262201004089\nShow more',
